ns bounded in $L^\\infty$, with\ncurvature in $L^{p}$, $p>n$, including semi-Riemannian metrics, and Lorentzian\nmetric connections of relativistic Physics. We interpret this as a\n``geometric'' improvement of the generalized Div-Curl Lemma. Our theory shows\nthat Uhlenbeck compactness and optimal regularity are pure logical consequences\nof the rule which defines how connections transform from one coordinate system\nto another -- what one could take to be the ``starting assumption of\ngeometry''.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 30 Dec 2019 16:41:15 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Sat, 25 Apr 2020 16:04:10 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Mon, 22 Jun 2020 14:33:41 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Fri, 6 Nov 2020 18:02:46 GMT"},{"version":"v5","created":"Thu, 25 Nov 2021 02:05:46 GMT"},{"version":"v6","created":"Wed, 1 Mar 2023 00:25:27 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-03-02"}
