Bi2Te4-terminated\nsurfaces and is applicable to all terminations of MnBi2nTe3n+1 family. Our\nfindings highlight the role of band hybridization, superior to magnetism in\nthis case, in shaping the general surface band structure in magnetic\ntopological materials for the first time.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 31 Dec 2019 09:31:21 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-12-24"}
